,Capricciosa is a type of pizza with a specific name. It includes toppings such as peperonata, olives, capers, mozzarella, anchovies, ham, and tomatoes. Specifically, a Capricciosa pizza combines tomato, ham, mozzarella, anchovies, olives, peperonata, and capers as its toppings. This type of pizza does not overlap with various other pizzas, including La Reine, Frutos do Mar, Fiorentina, Margherita, Sloppy Giuseppe, Veneziana, Americana Picante, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Pollo ad Astra, Caprina, Cajun, Giardiniera, Americana, Cobertura Prince Carlo, Siciliana, Parmense, Rosa, Soho, Quatro Queijos, and Napoletana.",31,True

,Cobertura de frango is a type of cobertura de carne. It is a type of something that at least has some spiciness but is not picante. Cobertura de frango does not overlap with cobertura de calabreza, cobertura de bife picante, or cobertura de presunto.",5,True

,Cobertura de carne is a type of cobertura da pizza. It does not overlap with cobertura de queijo, cobertura de frutas, cobertura de ervas, cobertura de peixe, cobertura de castanha, cobertura em molho, or cobertura de vegetais.",8,True
,Cobertura de anchovies is a type of cobertura de peixe. It does not overlap with cobertura de frutos do mar mistos, nor does it overlap with cobertura de camarao.",3,True

,Cajun is a type of pizza with a unique name. It is a type of pizza that exclusively has toppings such as mozzarella cheese, onion, peperonata, shrimp, tomato, and Tobasco pepper sauce. At a minimum, it includes toppings like Tobasco pepper sauce, onion, tomato, mozzarella cheese, peperonata, and shrimp. Cajun pizza does not overlap with other pizza types such as La Reine, Frutos do Mar, Fiorentina, Margherita, Veneziana, Americana Picante, Sloppy Giuseppe, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Caprina, Pollo ad Astra, Giardiniera, Americana, Prince Carlo, Capricciosa, Siciliana, Parmense, Rosa, Soho, Quatro Queijos, and Napoletana.",30,True

,Parmense is a type of pizza with a specific name. It is characterized by toppings that include a combination of tomato, asparagus, mozzarella, parmesan, and ham. At the very least, Parmense must have toppings of mozzarella, tomato, parmesan, asparagus, and ham. Parmense does not overlap with a variety of other pizzas, including La Reine, Frutos do Mar, Fiorentina, Margherita, Americana Picante, Veneziana, Sloppy Giuseppe, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Pollo ad Astra, Caprina, Cajun, Giardiniera, Americana, Cobertura Prince Carlo, Capricciosa, Siciliana, Rosa, Soho, Quatro Queijos, and Napoletana.",29,True

,Frutos do Mar is a type of pizza with a specific name. It is characterized by having toppings that include a combination of garlic topping, mixed seafood topping, and tomato topping. Additionally, Frutos do Mar must at least have some tomato topping, some mixed seafood topping, and some garlic topping. This pizza does not overlap with other pizzas such as La Reine, Fiorentina, Margherita, Sloppy Giuseppe, Veneziana, Americana Picante, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Pollo ad Astra, Caprina, Cajun, Giardiniera, Americana, Cobertura Prince Carlo, Capricciosa, Siciliana, Parmense, Rosa, Soho, Quatro Queijos, and Napoletana.",27,True

,Quatro queijos is a type of pizza with a name. It is a type of pizza that at least has toppings such as tomato, anchovies, mushrooms, calabrese, mozzarella, capers, and olives. Specifically, quatro queijos has a combination of these toppings: anchovies, capers, mozzarella, mushrooms, olives, calabrese, and tomato. Importantly, quatro queijos does not overlap with other pizza types such as la reine, frutos do mar, fiorentina, margherita, americana picante, veneziana, sloppy giuseppe, pizza aberta, cogumelo, caprina, pollo ad astra, cajun, giardiniera, americana, cobertura prince carlo, capricciosa, siciliana, parmense, rosa, soho, another quatro queijos, or napoletana.",31,True

,Napoletana is a type of pizza with a specific name. This pizza features at least some toppings of anchovies, mozzarella, capers, tomatoes, and olives. It exclusively includes the combination of these toppings: anchovies, capers, mozzarella, olives, and tomatoes.

The Napoletana pizza does not overlap with the following types of pizzas: La Reine, Frutos do Mar, Fiorentina, Margherita, Americana Picante, Sloppy Giuseppe, Veneziana, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Caprina, Pollo ad Astra, Cajun, Giardiniera, Americana, Cobertura Prince Carlo, Capricciosa, Siciliana, Parmense, Rosa, Soho, and Quatro Queijos.",29,True

Specifically, it only has toppings that are a combination of mozzarella and tomatoes. ,The Veneziana is a type of pizza with a specific name. It is characterized by having various toppings such as tomato sauce, capers, pine kernels, mozzarella, onions, and sultanas. Additionally, it includes olives as part of its toppings. The Veneziana exclusively has a combination of capers, mozzarella, olives, onions, pine kernels, sultanas, and tomato sauce. It does not share any similarities with other pizza types like La Reine, Frutos do Mar, Fiorentina, Margherita, Sloppy Giuseppe, Americana Picante, Pizza Aberta, Cogumelo, Pollo ad Astra, Caprina, Cajun, Giardiniera, Americana, Prince Carlo, Capricciosa, Siciliana, Parmense, Rosa, Soho, Quatro Queijos, and Napoletana.",31,True

,Fiorentina is a type of pizza that has a specific set of toppings. It includes mozzarella, garlic, spinach, tomato, olive, and Parmesan cheese. These toppings are essential and exclusive to Fiorentina, meaning it does not share or overlap with other types of pizzas. Fiorentina does not overlap with la reine, frutos do mar, margherita, americana picante, veneziana, sloppy giuseppe, pizza aberta, cogumelo, pollo ad astra, caprina, cajun, giardiniera, americana, cobertura prince carlo, capricciosa, siciliana, parmense, rosa, soho, quatro queijos, and napoletana.",30,True

,Quatro queijos is a type of pizza with a distinctive name. It is a type of pizza that at least has a topping of some ""cobertura quatro queijos."" Additionally, it is a type of pizza that only has toppings that are a combination of ""cobertura quatro queijos"" and ""cobertura de tomate."" Therefore, quatro queijos must also have a topping of some ""cobertura de tomate.""

Furthermore, quatro queijos does not overlap with several other types of pizza, including la reine, frutos do mar, fiorentina, margherita, veneziana, sloppy giuseppe, americana picante, pizza aberta, cogumelo, pollo ad astra, caprina, cajun, giardiniera, americana, cobertura prince carlo, capricciosa, siciliana, parmense, rosa, soho, napoletana, and even itself.",26,True

,Giardiniera is a type of pizza with a unique name. It features a variety of toppings, including mushrooms, leeks, peperonata, sliced tomatoes, mozzarella, olives, additional tomatoes, and petit pois. These toppings form a specific combination that includes leeks, mozzarella, mushrooms, olives, peperonata, petit pois, sliced tomatoes, and tomatoes. Giardiniera does not overlap with other pizzas such as la reine, frutos do mar, fiorentina, margherita, americana picante, sloppy giuseppe, veneziana, pizza aberta, cogumelo, pollo ad astra, caprina, cajun, americana, cobertura prince carlo, capricciosa, siciliana, parmense, rosa, soho, quatro queijos, and napoletana.",32,True
